   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">ignore the old pylofuf deck, i made this one a lot better than that one....... Use trygar first because he starts with pylofuf and tunneler&#39;s boots. Use trygar as a strong defense until u draw stronger creatures like korrits and parmalags. When u play korrit use him with parmalag using parmalags power so no energy is takin from ur creatures. using this combo can keep ur opponent down while you build up a defense line of pylofufs. if u play gum-gum slide him wiht pylofuf, pylofuf loses two and thats it. if gum-gum gets attacked again slide with the same pylofuf because it cant lose anymore energy and still hurts ur opponents creature. Dont use pack korrit unless u have atleast pack korrits and korrits in play because when u use pack korrits power ut kills him but if u have another pack korrit in play that one will have two and u can use its power without killing it, which in turn pumps up your korrit line. <br>
<br><br>
 Next use gogor, which probably wont be in for a long time because your goin to use his power a lot unless you get through the deck or draw spore vashp to get a pylofuf cause gogor doesnt hurt burrowed creatures. Burrow will also be a nice spell to get to keep ur creatures alive. a good idea would be to play cave rudwot and use crystal arboll on him and burrow him so he only loses two when he is attacked, but when his power goes into effect, he basically loses no energy which is a good defense. use power if u have no creatures or burrowed creatures in play so u have guys keepin u up, unless its an emergency. <br>
<br><br>
 last, use d&#39;jarvish, and by the time u get to him u should have gone through ur deck so u have all those nice cards back like pylofuf. if u get pylofuf play him as soon as possible and keep adding energy to him with c. arboll and enrich. if it gets shockwaved, dont worry cause d&#39;jarvish&#39;s effect will bring it back to ur hand. if u get tunnelers boots it will be good cause his other effect adds one energy to all burrowed creatures at the end of ur turn, same as tunnelers boots, and if u play that, u will add 2 to all ur burrowed  creatures. <br>
<br><br>
 this deck does drive ur opponent nutz sum times with all the burrowed stuff, which is very fun =)<br>
<br><br>
  i hope u like this deck as much as i do, underneath is the best!  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
